<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1906-07-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1906-07-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="684" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d684">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.—Extracts.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1906-07-13"><hi rend="italic">July 13,
                                1906</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Brown reports he has just had a conference with President Estrada,
                            who accepts in principle the proposal of peace, but doubts good faith of
                            Salvador, and insists the agreement to disarm and negotiate must be
                            pledged satisfactorily to the United States Government. Instructions are
                            requested.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>